 (1) To access the root privileges

	$ sudo -i
	or
	$ su -
	or
	$ su
	
	to log out from root mode
	$ exit

 (2) Changing the password of root
 
 	$ passwd
 	if there is a Authentication error then type following
 	$ sudo -i passwd
 	
 (3) Reading a file page by page
  
  	$ more filename
  	
 (4) sorting
 
 	$ sort filename
 	Sort filename in Ascii of first character of sentence order and prints
 	
 	$ sort -r filename
 	sort in the reverse order
 	
 	$ sort -n filename
 	sort the file containg numerical data in ascending order
 	
 	$ sort -f filename
 	case insensitive sorting
 	
 	$ sort -n -r filename
 	sort numerical file in descending order
 	
 	$ sort file >> newFile
 	sort the file and then copies to newFile
 	
 	$ sort file > newFile
 	sort the file and then overwrite to newFile
 	
 (5) Renaming and moving the files
 
 	$ mv oldname newname
 	Renames the file
 	
 	$ mv oldname newname
 	Renames the dir
 	
 	$ mv file directory
 	Moves file from current dir to specified dir
 	
 	$ mv dir destinationDir
 	Moves dir to specified location
 	
 (6) Copy files and dir
 
 	$ cp srcFile destDir
 	
 	$ cp -r srcDir destDir
 	
 (7) Printing on Console
 
 	$ echo msg
 	
 (8) Present Working Dir
 
 	$ pwd
 
 
